items.title: Awesome Ant Design
items.content_text:
### Non-JavaScript Libraries / Themes

*   [syn-antd](https://gitlab.com/synqrinus/syn-antd) - Ant Design wrapper for [ClojureScript](https://clojurescript.org/) and [Reagent (⭐4.8k)](https://github.com/reagent-project/reagent) using [shadow-cljs](http://shadow-cljs.org/) with tree-shaking support. As with other ClojureScript libraries, it cross-compiles to JavaScript.
items.content_html:
Non-JavaScript Libraries / Themes

  • syn-antd - Ant Design wrapper for ClojureScript and Reagent (⭐4.8k) using shadow-cljs with tree-shaking support. As with other ClojureScript libraries, it cross-compiles to JavaScript.

items.title: Awesome Scientific Computing
items.content_text:
### Finite Elements

*   [SfePy](https://sfepy.org) - Simple Finite Elements in Python.
    (Python, BSD, [GitHub (⭐797)](https://github.com/sfepy/sfepy))

### Meshing / Triangular and tetrahedral meshing

*   [trimesh](https://trimesh.org) - Loading and using triangular meshes with an emphasis on watertight surfaces.
    (Python, MIT, [GitHub (⭐3.3k)](https://github.com/mikedh/trimesh))

### Community / Mesh tools

*   [Wolfgang Bangerth's video class](https://www.math.colostate.edu/~bangerth/videos.html) - MATH 676: Finite element methods in scientific computing.
items.content_html:
Finite Elements

  • SfePy - Simple Finite Elements in Python. (Python, BSD, GitHub (⭐797))

Meshing / Triangular and tetrahedral meshing

  • trimesh - Loading and using triangular meshes with an emphasis on watertight surfaces. (Python, MIT, GitHub (⭐3.3k))

Community / Mesh tools
